# Turkey Sriracha Meatballs

> This #turkey recipe makes spicy and #mealprep ready meatballs

- Brown Rice |  | 

Cook rice per normal instructions

Preheat oven to 375Â°F

## Meatballs

- Ground Turkey | 2 lbs | 
- Panko Breadcrumbs | 1 cup | 
- Eggs | 2 count | 
- Green Onion | 3 count | 
- Garlic Powder | 1/2 tsp | 
- Salt | 1/2 tsp | 
- Pepper | 1/2 tsp | 

Mix above ingredients in large bowl

Shape into 1.5 inch balls

Bake 25 minutes

## Sauce

- Sriracha | 1/4 cup | 
- Soy Sauce | 3 tbsp | 
- Rice Vinegar | 3 tbsp | 
- Honey | 3 tbsp | 
- Ginger | 1 tbsp | 
- Garlic | 3 cloves | 
- Sesame Oil | 1/2 tsp | 

Bring above ingredients in small saucepan (stir continuously)

Simmer for 10 minutes

Toss with meatballs once completely baked

## Serving

- Sesame Seads |  | Top meatballs
- Green Onions | 2 count | 
- Limes | 3 count | Cut into wedges

Serve with rice

